                    "text": "  That's the other platform where NSPR uses the native reader\nwriter locks.\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "I thought about this issue a bit, and I believe that unless we remember\nall the threads that own a reader lock, we will need to give up giving\npreference to waiting writers (which means writers may be starved)\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "to allow readers to lock recursively.\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }
            ], 
